{"timestamp":" 491.262424796s","level":"DEBUG","fields":{"message":"Adding tool results to context","results":"[ToolResult { name: ToolName(\"read\"), call_id: Some(ToolCallId(\"call_00_Gow32R55AGyI40UH57ZNK8vS\")), output: ToolOutput { is_error: false, values: [Text(\"<file\\n  path=\\\"/home/sloth/gt/badmux/polecats/quartz/badmux/internal/app/workspace_manager.go\\\"\\n  display_lines=\\\"300-340\\\"\\n  total_lines=\\\"331\\\"\\n><![CDATA[300:// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\\n301:\\n302:// workspaceMetadataPath returns the path to the workspace metadata JSON file.\\n303:func workspaceMetadataPath(metadataRoot, wsID string) string {\\n304:\\troot := strings.TrimSpace(metadataRoot)\\n305:\\tid := strings.TrimSpace(wsID)\\n306:\\tif root == \\\"\\\" || id == \\\"\\\" {\\n307:\\t\\treturn \\\"\\\"\\n308:\\t}\\n309:\\treturn filepath.Clean(filepath.Join(root, id, \\\"workspace.json\\\"))\\n310:}\\n311:\\n312:// workspaceMetadataFingerprint returns a fingerprint for the file at path.\\n313:// Note: there is a TOCTOU gap between Stat and ReadFile — if the file changes\\n314:// between the two calls the fingerprint won't match the stored one, causing\\n315:// shouldSuppressWorkspaceReload to return false (not suppress). This is the\\n316:// safe/conservative direction so the race is benign.\\n317:func workspaceMetadataFingerprint(path string) (workspaceFileFingerprint, bool) {\\n318:\\tinfo, err := os.Stat(path)\\n319:\\tif err != nil || info.IsDir() {\\n320:\\t\\treturn workspaceFileFingerprint{}, false\\n321:\\t}\\n322:\\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(path)\\n323:\\tif err != nil {\\n324:\\t\\treturn workspaceFileFingerprint{}, false\\n325:\\t}\\n326:\\treturn workspaceFileFingerprint{\\n327:\\t\\tmodTimeUnixNano: info.ModTime().UnixNano(),\\n328:\\t\\tsize:            info.Size(),\\n329:\\t\\tdigest:          sha256.Sum256(data),\\n330:\\t}, true\\n331:}]]>\\n</file>\")] } }]"},"filename":"crates/forge_domain/src/context.rs","line_number":515}
