{"timestamp":"  39.751966076s","level":"DEBUG","fields":{"message":"Adding tool results to context","results":"[ToolResult { name: ToolName(\"shell\"), call_id: Some(ToolCallId(\"call_00_LR8FNkpUV7d73F3i6Rau3cQE\")), output: ToolOutput { is_error: false, values: [Text(\"<shell_output\\n  command=\\\"bd show bmx-6lo 2>&1\\\"\\n  shell=\\\"/usr/bin/zsh\\\"\\n  description=\\\"Get bead details using mol ID\\\"\\n  exit_code=\\\"0\\\"\\n>\\n<stdout\\n  total_lines=\\\"79\\\"\\n><![CDATA[◇ bmx-6lo · bmx-e02.4b: Move workspace lifecycle handler bodies into WorkspaceManager   [● P2 · HOOKED]\\nOwner: Megatherium · Assignee: badmux/polecats/quartz · Type: task\\nCreated: 2026-04-29 · Updated: 2026-04-29\\n\\nDESCRIPTION\\nattached_molecule: bmx-wisp-lgat attached_formula: mol-polecat-work attached_at:\\n2026-04-29T21:31:54Z dispatched_by: mayor                                       \\n                                                                                \\nWHAT: Move the bodies of 11 workspace lifecycle handler methods from App into   \\nWorkspaceManager methods, then update app_input.go to delegate.                 \\n                                                                                \\nWHICH HANDLERS: Creation flow (app_input_workspace.go):                         \\n                                                                                \\nhandleWorkspaceCreated (line 46) → WorkspaceManager.HandleWorkspaceCreated      \\nhandleWorkspaceCreatedWithWarning (line 32) → WorkspaceManager.                 \\nHandleWorkspaceCreatedWithWarning                                               \\nhandleWorkspaceSetupComplete (line 60) → WorkspaceManager.                      \\nHandleWorkspaceSetupComplete                                                    \\nhandleWorkspaceCreateFailed (line 68) → WorkspaceManager.                       \\nHandleWorkspaceCreateFailed                                                     \\nhandleCreateWorkspace (app_input_messages_workspace.go:262) → WorkspaceManager. \\nHandleCreateWorkspace                                                           \\n                                                                                \\nDeletion flow (app_input_workspace.go):                                         \\n                                                                                \\nhandleDeleteWorkspace (line 14) → WorkspaceManager.HandleDeleteWorkspace        \\nhandleWorkspaceDeleted (line 83) → WorkspaceManager.HandleWorkspaceDeleted      \\nhandleWorkspaceDeleteFailed (line 113) → WorkspaceManager.                      \\nHandleWorkspaceDeleteFailed                                                     \\n                                                                                \\nPersistence (app_persistence.go + app_input.go):                                \\n                                                                                \\nhandlePersistDebounce (app_persistence.go:77) → WorkspaceManager.               \\nHandlePersistDebounce                                                           \\nhandleTabDetached (app_input.go:387) → WorkspaceManager.HandleTabDetached       \\n                                                                                \\nWHY: WorkspaceManager already owns the dirty-tracking, delete-in-flight guards, \\nand creation-tracking state (workspace_manager.go). These 11 handlers are the   \\nconsumers of that state — they call wm().clearCreatingWorkspace(),              \\nwm().markWorkspaceDeleteInFlight(), etc. Moving the bodies into WorkspaceManager\\ncompletes the encapsulation: the manager owns both the state AND the message    \\nprocessing for workspace lifecycle.                                             \\n                                                                                \\nNEW DEPENDENCIES WorkspaceManager will need:                                    \\n                                                                                \\nworkspaceService — for create/delete/save                                       \\nDashboard model ref — for SetWorkspaceCreating, SetWorkspaceDeleting, Update    \\nToast model ref — for error/warning toasts                                      \\nCenter model ref — for GetTabsInfoForWorkspace, DetachTabByID, Update           \\nSidebarTerminal model ref — for Update                                          \\nGitStatusService — for Invalidate                                               \\nCallback functions: loadProjects, runSetupAsync, persistWorkspaceTabs,          \\npersistActiveWorkspaceTabs, cleanupWorkspaceTmuxSessions                        \\nHelper functions: findWorkspaceByID, markLocalWorkspaceSaveForID                \\n                                                                                \\nRISK: MEDIUM. This is the biggest change. WorkspaceManager goes from a pure     \\ndata-tracking struct to a message-handling controller. Must avoid creating a    \\nsecond god object — only inject what the workspace lifecycle handlers actually  \\nneed, not everything on App.                                                    \\n                                                                                \\nNote: handleProjectsLoaded and handleWorkspaceActivated are intentionally LEFT  \\non App. They are cross-cutting orchestrators that span workspaces, tmux, git,   \\ntickets, and UI. They will be addressed in bmx-gzm.1 (Move workspace logic to   \\ninternal/app/workspaces).                                                       \\n                                                                                \\nNo new files.                                                                   \\n\\n\\nPARENT\\n  ↑ ○ bmx-e02: (EPIC) Decompose App God Object ● P2\\n\\nDEPENDS ON\\n  → ✓ bmx-e02.1: Extract WorkspaceManager ● P2\\n  → ✓ bmx-e02.2: Extract GitStatusController ● P2\\n  → ○ bmx-wisp-lgat: (EPIC) mol-polecat-work ● P2\\n\\nBLOCKS\\n  ← ○ bmx-gzm.1: Move workspace logic to internal/app/workspaces ● P2\\n]]>\\n</stdout>\\n</shell_output>\")] } }, ToolResult { name: ToolName(\"shell\"), call_id: Some(ToolCallId(\"call_01_rCDxHIvK7c983BsR2NPlQBX7\")), output: ToolOutput { is_error: false, values: [Text(\"<shell_output\\n  command=\\\"bd list --limit 20 2>&1\\\"\\n  shell=\\\"/usr/bin/zsh\\\"\\n  description=\\\"List recent beads to find our issue\\\"\\n  exit_code=\\\"0\\\"\\n>\\n<stdout\\n  total_lines=\\\"30\\\"\\n><![CDATA[○ bmx-badmux-polecat-obsidian ● P2 bmx-badmux-polecat-obsidian\\n○ bmx-badmux-polecat-quartz ● P2 bmx-badmux-polecat-quartz\\n○ bmx-badmux-refinery ● P2 Refinery for badmux - processes merge queue.\\n○ bmx-badmux-witness ● P2 Witness for badmux - monitors polecat health and progress.\\n○ bmx-c7z ● P2 [epic] Enforce Strict TEA State Flow\\n├── ○ bmx-c7z.1 ● P2 Refactor center.Model to eliminate atomic state\\n└── ○ bmx-c7z.2 ● P2 Refactor AgentManager to emit TEA messages\\n○ bmx-e02 ● P2 [epic] Decompose App God Object\\n├── ◇ bmx-6lo ● P2 bmx-e02.4b: Move workspace lifecycle handler bodies into WorkspaceManager\\n└── ◇ bmx-84d ● P2 bmx-e02.4c: Move dialog/handling handler bodies into UICompositor\\n○ bmx-f12 ● P2 [epic] Epic: Phase 5 — UI Integration\\n○ bmx-gzm ● P2 [epic] Sub-package internal/app monolith\\n├── ○ bmx-gzm.1 ● P2 Move workspace logic to internal/app/workspaces\\n├── ○ bmx-gzm.2 ● P2 Move UI orchestration to internal/app/orchestrator\\n└── ○ bmx-gzm.3 ● P2 Define internal interfaces for package boundaries\\n○ bmx-lib ● P2 Check all help texts for correctness and completion\\n○ bmx-wisp-gsp6 ● P2 [epic] mol-polecat-work\\n└── ◇ bmx-84d ● P2 bmx-e02.4c: Move dialog/handling handler bodies into UICompositor\\n◇ bmx-wisp-hq7s ● P2 [epic] mol-refinery-patrol\\n○ bmx-wisp-lgat ● P2 [epic] mol-polecat-work\\n└── ◇ bmx-6lo ● P2 bmx-e02.4b: Move workspace lifecycle handler bodies into WorkspaceManager\\n○ bmx-zlc ● P2 [epic] Implement Architectural Linting\\n├── ○ bmx-zlc.1 ● P2 Add gocyclo and funlen linters\\n└── ○ bmx-zlc.2 ● P2 Integrate depguard for strict boundaries\\n○ bmx-sz9 ● P3 Port blunderbust tests to amux\\n\\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\\nTotal: 23 issues (20 open, 0 in progress)\\n\\nStatus: ○ open  ◐ in_progress  ● blocked  ✓ closed  ❄ deferred]]>\\n</stdout>\\n</shell_output>\")] } }]"},"filename":"crates/forge_domain/src/context.rs","line_number":515}
